    • Constructor Detail

      • SerialPortIKBusConnection

        public SerialPortIKBusConnection(String portName)
                          throws IKBusIOException
        Creates a new I/K-bus connection that uses the serial port with the specified name to establish a communication link. When the constructor is invoked the port will be opened immediately using the correct serial communication parameters for the I/K-bus protocol. Hardware flow control will also be enabled automatically using the RS-232 RTS and CTS pins. After successful instantiation of a SerialPortIKBusConnection a communication link is opened immediately, so there is no option to explicitly open the connection. Via the close() method the communication link can be closed. The names of the serial ports that are available on the system can be retrieved via the getAvailableSerialPorts() method. Note that the port names vary per operation system.
        Parameters:
        portName - System name of the serial port for which an I/K-bus communication link is to be opened.
        Throws:
        IKBusIOException - If an I/O error occurs while trying to open the serial port.

        public static String[] getAvailableSerialPorts()
        Retrieves the names of the serial ports that are available on the system. When no serial ports are available on the system an empty array will be returned.
        Returns:
        An array containing the names of the serial ports that are available.
